✅ HR Dashboard – Description

An HR Dashboard is an interactive data visualization tool that helps the Human Resources (HR) team monitor, analyze, and manage key employee-related metrics in real time. It provides a single centralized platform where HR managers can track workforce performance, hiring status, attendance, employee satisfaction, and other important HR operations.

The dashboard displays insights through charts, graphs, and tables, enabling quick decision-making and improving overall HR efficiency.

⭐ Key Features of the HR Dashboard
1. Employee Overview

Total employees

New hires vs. exits

Department-wise employee distribution

2. Attendance & Leave Tracking

Daily/Monthly attendance trends

Absenteeism rate

Leave applications (approved/rejected/pending)

3. Recruitment Analytics

Open positions

Application status (screened, shortlisted, selected, rejected)

Hiring timeline & recruitment funnel

4. Payroll Insights

Salary distribution

Overtime analysis

Monthly payouts summary

5. Performance Management

Performance ratings

Top performers

Training completion rate

6. Employee Satisfaction

Feedback scores

Survey insights

Workplace engagement metrics
